Letting Go
Jeremy Camp
Key: C
CCLI: 4505039
Copyright: 2004 Thirsty Moon River Publishing / Stolen Pride

Capo: 4th fret

I dunno what to call this chord but the C#m is like a dimished chord?
If my music theory serves me correct the E in the chord is dropped to a D#, 
I'll call it C2 Diminished.   So the fingering would look like this:


C2dim: starting 4th fret
E--0-----|-----|-----|-----|
B--|--1--|-----|-----|-----|
G--|-----|-----|-----|--4--|
D--|-----|--2--|-----|-----|
A--0-----|-----|-----|-----|
E--|-----|-----|-----|-----|


In this tab I will use the chords as if there was no capo so: C#m = Am  and G#m = E and so forth.
So the A minor is dimished.
Here goes...


Chords:
Am Dim	- x02410
Em7	- 022030
F/A	- 003010 or 003210
F2	- 033010
G	- 320033
C5	- x355xx
Cdim	- x354xx




Intro-Chords: ( AmDim  Em F/A )  x2


(Please Note:  Tablature will not transpose on this website)
Intro Tab:
With Capo on 4th fret

